Sentencas: In order to obtain the high conductivity values and wide spinel stability region for solid oxide fuel cell interconnect, several multilayer Ni, Co and Mn coatings are electroplated and then oxidized in air to form spinel oxide layers.
Titulo: Structure and properties of composite Ni-Co-Mn coatings on metal interconnects by electrodeposition

Sentencas: Potentiodynamic polarization curves in different simple solutions are tested to analyze the deposition behavior of Co and Mn.
Titulo: Structure and properties of composite Ni-Co-Mn coatings on metal interconnects by electrodeposition

Sentencas: Microstructures and compositions of Ni-Co-Mn multilayers by adjusting the thickness and deposition parameters are analyzed by X-ray diffraction (XRD) and scanning electron microscopy (SEM).
Titulo: Structure and properties of composite Ni-Co-Mn coatings on metal interconnects by electrodeposition

Sentencas: The results show that area specific resistance value of sample B-Ni/Co after oxidation at 750 degrees C for 500h is the lowest among the coatings, and the resistance values at 700 degrees C and 800 degrees C are 35.3 and 31.7 m Omega.cm(2), respectively.
Titulo: Structure and properties of composite Ni-Co-Mn coatings on metal interconnects by electrodeposition

Sentencas: When the Ni transition layer in the vicinity of coating/substrate interface is thick, it will lead to the outward diffusion and aggregation of element Fe to form Ferich oxide intermediate layer, which will affect the high-temperature performance of the coating.
Titulo: Structure and properties of composite Ni-Co-Mn coatings on metal interconnects by electrodeposition

Sentencas: Pure Co and CoMn alloy coatings with a certain thickness can effectively prevent the inward diffusion of oxygen and the outward diffusion of Fe and Cr at high temperature.
Titulo: Structure and properties of composite Ni-Co-Mn coatings on metal interconnects by electrodeposition

Sentencas: The thin Ni transition layer combined with the thick Co layer or CoMn layer has the best element diffusion inhibition and high temperature electrical properties during the long-term high-temperature oxidation process.
Titulo: Structure and properties of composite Ni-Co-Mn coatings on metal interconnects by electrodeposition
